  "correctAnswer": 1,
  "explanation": [
    "Using $\\sqrt{1+\\sin x} = \\sqrt{(\\sin(x/2) + \\cos(x/2))^2} = |\\sin(x/2) + \\cos(x/2)|$.",
    "In $[0, \\pi/2]$, both are positive.",
    "$\\int (\\sin(x/2) + \\cos(x/2)) dx = [-2\\cos(x/2) + 2\\sin(x/2)]_0^{\\pi/2}$.",
    "Upper: $-2\\cos(\\pi/4) + 2\\sin(\\pi/4) = -2(1/\\sqrt{2}) + 2(1/\\sqrt{2}) = 0$.",
    "Lower: $-2(1) + 0 = -2$.",
    "Result: $0 - (-2) = 2$."
  ]
